1
00:01:25,461 --> 00:01:28,463
(birds chirping)

2
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:30,715
Man:
"Dear Ryan,

3
00:01:30,883 --> 00:01:34,552
I reckon you're feeling lonely
now that your mother is gone.

4
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,680
You're too young
for something like this.

5
00:01:37,848 --> 00:01:40,057
I know she must've
told you about me,

6
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:42,727
and I for one never stopped
thinking about you.

7
00:01:42,895 --> 00:01:45,021
Even though
I've never seen you,

8
00:01:45,189 --> 00:01:48,733
I bet my best memories
I'd recognize you in the blackest night.

9
00:01:48,901 --> 00:01:52,487
These past years
have been hard on us all.

10
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:55,990
Very few of us
are still around.

11
00:01:56,158 --> 00:01:58,951
The land where I live now
is a good one...

12
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:02,789
quiet people,
peaceful for the most part.

13
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,666
But it's not home.

14
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:09,712
That's why it's time for me
to come back.

15
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:12,006
Burn this letter
after you read it,

16
00:02:12,174 --> 00:02:14,008
like your mother
would've done,

17
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:16,344
and wait for me.

18
00:02:16,512 --> 00:02:20,306
Much love, your uncle."

19
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:48,417
(giggling)

20
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:50,962
(man shouting)

21
00:03:10,482 --> 00:03:12,692
(speaking Spanish)
I can't come tomorrow.

22
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:21,868
We need you to pay us
for this week's work.

23
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:26,205
And for the seeds too.
You never paid for them.

24
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:30,126
You know where the money is.
Just take it.

25
00:03:30,294 --> 00:03:31,294
No.

26
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:33,254
You're the boss.

27
00:03:33,422 --> 00:03:35,548
You have to give it to me.

28
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:38,843
I can't take it.
That would be wrong.

29
00:03:39,845 --> 00:03:41,637
I'm not your wife.

30
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,224
Sure.

31
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,938
You're right, Yana.

32
00:03:53,275 --> 00:03:54,525
You're right.

33
00:03:58,196 --> 00:04:00,406
(thunder rumbling)

34
00:04:01,408 --> 00:04:02,867
I have rain gear.

35
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:08,789
Mr. James, you're going away,
aren't you?

36
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:13,252
My mother says all gringos leave
once they have enough money.

37
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:17,548
You're a gringo,
but you don't have that much money.

38
00:04:19,051 --> 00:04:22,678
I'll have enough
after selling the horses.

39
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:26,599
Take care, Yana.

40
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:29,352
I'll see you
when I'm back from Potosi.

41
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:32,063
Then I'll leave for good.

