♪ Ain't no grave ♪

65
00:06:11,997 --> 00:06:13,956
♪ Can hold my body down. ♪

66
00:06:20,756 --> 00:06:23,841
- (newsboy shouting)
- (church bell ringing)

67
00:06:25,427 --> 00:06:26,719
Take care of him.

68
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,390
(car horn honks)

69
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:17,561
I'm withdrawing all my money.

70
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:20,314
In dollars, please.

71
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:36,247
Mr. Blackthorn,

72
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:38,666
have we done anything
to upset you?

73
00:07:38,834 --> 00:07:41,252
Well, you know,
there is just one thing.

74
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:45,673
I can't remember ever being
so well received at a bank before.

75
00:07:45,841 --> 00:07:48,342
Buenos dias.

76
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:19,999
(piano music playing)

77
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:23,169
Your whisky, sir.
American.

78
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,712
Here. Thanks.

79
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:28,716
Americans are
creatures of habit.

80
00:08:28,884 --> 00:08:31,635
They have excellent
scotch here, French cognac,

81
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:33,637
but Mr. Blackthorn here

82
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:35,890
likes to stick to his
old gringo whisky.

83
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:38,475
Yeah, it just seems
to haunt me, you know.

84
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:40,895
To a fine sale.

85
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,646
Gracias.

86
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:45,316
You have quite a talent
for breeding horses.

87
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:48,027
Those horses will be the envy
of many men around here.

88
00:08:48,195 --> 00:08:50,821
But you'd think
that here in Bolivia,

89
00:08:50,989 --> 00:08:52,948
with so many bloody Indians,

90
00:08:53,116 --> 00:08:54,783
it would be simple
to find good horses.

91
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,745
Indians got nothing
to do with it.

92
00:08:57,913 --> 00:09:00,289
The terrain's too rugged here

93
00:09:00,457 --> 00:09:02,458
for good horses, too high.

94
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:07,588
I was wondering if maybe
you all would like to play

95
00:09:07,756 --> 00:09:09,757
a few rounds of cards.

96
00:09:09,925 --> 00:09:12,218
What do you think?

97
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:14,345
Yes, we're in.

98
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,138
You know, I miss
a good game of cards

99
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:18,349
out on the ranch.

100
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:21,769
Ain't nothing but a goddamn bunch
of Indians out there, you know.

101
00:09:21,937 --> 00:09:25,856
There's no civilized folk
like yourselves.

102
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,101
(whistles)

103
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:28,752
(flies buzzing)

104
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:01,243
- (gunshot)
- (horse neighs)

105
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:08,709
Easy.

106
00:11:08,877 --> 00:11:12,087
Don't leave me now, Cinco.

107
00:11:12,255 --> 00:11:13,672
(snorts)

108
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,341
Whoa.

109
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:16,842
Easy, buddy.

110
00:11:19,554 --> 00:11:21,764
Oh, easy, buddy.

111
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:23,223
(man speaking Spanish)
Don't move!

112
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:25,059
- (gunshot)
- (horse neighs)

113
00:11:26,186 --> 00:11:27,686
- Come here, horse.
- (cocks gun)

114
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:28,937
That's it.

115
00:11:31,775 --> 00:11:33,067
Man: Hiya!

116
00:11:34,611 --> 00:11:38,655
- (horse neighs)
- (man grunting)

117
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:43,494
No. (whistles)

118
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:44,995
Cinco!

119
00:11:45,163 --> 00:11:46,914
(whistles) Hey!

120
00:11:47,082 --> 00:11:51,126
Whoa! Cinco!

121
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,588
God damn it!

122
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:03,472
- I'm out of bullets.
- Get up.

123
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:42,553
(grunts)

124
00:12:47,142 --> 00:12:48,142
Please.

125
00:12:50,061 --> 00:12:52,104
I'm freezing.

126
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:53,272
Are you Chilean?

127
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:56,942
Spanish.

128
00:12:57,944 --> 00:12:59,278
Conquistador!

129
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,697
I just came here to work.

130
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:08,912
Are you going to kill me?

131
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:11,457
Oh, so you speak English.

132
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:15,586
You got any idea
where in the world we are?

133
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:19,089
Huh? We're in the middle
of nowhere.

134
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:21,884
My entire future ran off
with that horse,

135
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:25,345
everything I've got...
$6000 to get me back home.

136
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,806
The horse alone's worth $500.

137
00:13:27,974 --> 00:13:30,350
Now I've got your miserable
life on my hands.

138
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,311
Ain't worth a nickel.

139
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:34,313
I'm sorry.

140
00:13:34,481 --> 00:13:36,940
I thought you were after me.

141
00:13:37,108 --> 00:13:40,444
Please, I just want
to live a little longer.

142
00:13:40,612 --> 00:13:43,071
You do, huh?

143
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:55,292
Be my guest.

144
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:10,807
Man: Eat.

145
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:13,519
Eat, you
flea-ridden coward.

146
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:17,397
It was just a little jump.
(grunts)

147
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:20,317
"The best horses."
Filthy hag.

148
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:22,319
(grunts)

149
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:25,405
I'll run you all the way
from here to El Paso.

150
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:36,291
Oh shit.

151
00:14:38,461 --> 00:14:40,546
Come on.

152
00:14:48,555 --> 00:14:51,765
(gunshots)

153
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:54,434
What the hell
are you doing, Butch?

154
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:57,271
Not the best place to rest.

155
00:14:57,438 --> 00:14:59,982
- It has a nice view.
- (chuckles)

156
00:15:09,784 --> 00:15:12,286
(gunshots)

157
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:15,163
Oh, she's handy.

158
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:17,416
You teach her?

159
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:21,003
I don't think anybody
ever taught her anything.

160
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:23,213
And it's about time
you learned her name.

161
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:31,388
Kid, I think it's time
for us to go.

162
00:15:31,556 --> 00:15:33,390
Don't worry.
Those were the last.

163
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:35,434
You're not listening.

164
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:38,103
I mean go as in leave,

165
00:15:38,271 --> 00:15:41,857
go to South America now.

166
00:15:46,821 --> 00:15:49,406
Butch wants to leave,

167
00:15:49,574 --> 00:15:52,159
go to South America.

168
00:15:52,327 --> 00:15:54,661
And he wants me
to go with him.

169
00:15:54,829 --> 00:15:56,747
Why are you telling me?

170
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:59,374
I think it might be
a good idea...

171
00:15:59,542 --> 00:16:01,835
the three of us...

172
00:16:02,003 --> 00:16:04,379
that's all.

173
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:11,261
It's a great idea.

174
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:47,714
(cocks gun)

175
00:16:52,762 --> 00:16:55,931
You're pushing
your luck, son.

176
00:16:57,934 --> 00:17:00,352
Please.

177
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:04,106
They have been
following me for days.

178
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,691
I need your help.

179
00:17:43,438 --> 00:17:46,440
All right, now you
can be on your way.

180
00:17:48,151 --> 00:17:49,985
Taypi is only about 15 miles

181
00:17:50,153 --> 00:17:52,112
down the tracks here.
You just follow it.

182
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:54,990
Even if I make it,
they'll catch me

183
00:17:55,158 --> 00:17:56,992
and they'll kill me.

184
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:59,327
Well, good for them,
whoever they are.

185
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,413
- (gunshot)
- I'm not gonna repeat myself,

186
00:18:01,581 --> 00:18:05,500
you son of a bitch.
Get up and get down the tracks.

187
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:07,502
Please.

188
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:10,464
Have pity and help me.

189
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:16,344
I can give you
your money back.

190
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:19,473
I have the money,
but it's hidden.

191
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,683
That's why they're after me.

192
00:18:24,687 --> 00:18:28,023
You'd better not be
playing me, you bastard.

193
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:35,197
Man: It's two or three days
on horseback from here...

194
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:37,574
an abandoned mine.

195
00:18:37,742 --> 00:18:39,576
I'm an engineer.

196
00:18:39,744 --> 00:18:41,411
I work at the tin mines.

197
00:18:41,579 --> 00:18:43,455
That's why I came over
from Spain.

198
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:45,957
When we get there,
I'll give you

199
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,043
your money back.
I promise.

200
00:18:48,211 --> 00:18:50,545
That's not good enough.

201
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:56,927
I stole from the mine
I was working at in Oruro.

202
00:18:57,094 --> 00:19:00,263
Those mines are well-guarded.
Patiño owns all that.

203
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,351
Yeah.

204
00:19:04,519 --> 00:19:07,187
You stole from Simon Patiño?

205
00:19:08,439 --> 00:19:12,359
You're plowing
in high cotton, boy.

206
00:19:12,527 --> 00:19:15,111
Can I have a drink?

207
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:23,119
Patiño, huh?

208
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:26,581
Yes.

209
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:28,583
I robbed the Suyana Mine.

210
00:19:28,751 --> 00:19:30,252
Patiño... you know him?

211
00:19:30,419 --> 00:19:32,170
I know snakes,

212
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:35,298
no matter what hole
they crawl out of.

213
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:43,056
- How many's following you?
- I don't know.

214
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:45,767
A dozen maybe.
I'm not sure.

215
00:19:45,935 --> 00:19:47,769
How far back are they?

216
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:51,189
A day or two.

217
00:19:51,357 --> 00:19:53,817
Not anymore.

218
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:26,975
Who are you?

219
00:20:27,143 --> 00:20:29,352
My name is Eduardo.

220
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:32,772
How much money
did you steal, Eduardo?

221
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,191
Not much.
Just enough to...

222
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:38,069
Nobody steals not much
from the richest man on the continent.

223
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:40,447
Now how much
did you steal?

224
00:20:40,615 --> 00:20:43,325
£10,000 sterling.

225
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:46,453
$50,000 American,
more or less.

226
00:20:46,621 --> 00:20:49,122
Yeah, well, that's
$25,000 for me then.

227
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:50,749
But you said $6,000.

228
00:20:50,917 --> 00:20:54,169
Look, the only reason
that you're alive

229
00:20:54,337 --> 00:20:56,379
is that you might have
some money.

230
00:20:56,547 --> 00:20:58,089
Now you owe me half.

231
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:00,508
You owe me for every step
I take without a horse,

232
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:03,261
every hour I go without water.
And you also owe me

233
00:21:03,429 --> 00:21:06,598
for not shooting your sorry ass
the first time I saw you.

234
00:21:06,766 --> 00:21:08,350
- Do you understand?
- Yeah.

235
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:10,936
Now shut the fuck up
and just follow me.

236
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:30,455
(Eduardo speaking Spanish)
Fuck!

237
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:33,500
Four days without a hat.

238
00:21:33,668 --> 00:21:36,378
This plateau sun is killing me.

239
00:21:37,672 --> 00:21:40,298
James:
Meet me at the cantina.

240
00:21:40,466 --> 00:21:42,801
(door closes)

241
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:46,930
Keeper.

242
00:21:47,974 --> 00:21:49,391
We only have chicha.

243
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:52,060
No. I want a pitcher of water.

244
00:21:52,228 --> 00:21:54,062
There's only chicha.

245
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:55,522
Yeah...

246
00:22:01,278 --> 00:22:02,946
Two Bolivianos.

247
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:23,341
(chuckles)

248
00:22:23,509 --> 00:22:26,386
(speaks Aymara)

249
00:22:26,554 --> 00:22:28,471
(speaking Spanish)
Gimme a drink.

250
00:22:28,639 --> 00:22:31,808
And I want
two boxes of ammunition too.

251
00:22:31,976 --> 00:22:32,976
The same as yours.

252
00:22:33,144 --> 00:22:34,561
- I only have one.
- Okay.

253
00:22:35,730 --> 00:22:36,730
Thanks.

254
00:22:39,275 --> 00:22:41,985
I bought us
a couple of mules.

255
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:43,820
That's all there is
around here.

256
00:22:43,988 --> 00:22:46,990
At least buy me a drink.
You'll soon be rich.

257
00:22:47,158 --> 00:22:49,868
Nice pistol.

258
00:22:58,836 --> 00:23:02,047
I should thank you.
I could have died.

259
00:23:02,214 --> 00:23:04,132
The plateau is like hell.

260
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,176
You got no business
judging this land.

261
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:08,595
And I'm not
helping you either.

262
00:23:08,763 --> 00:23:11,139
I'm just trying
to get back what's mine.

263
00:23:11,307 --> 00:23:13,183
Okay.

264
00:23:15,144 --> 00:23:16,770
So what do we do now?

265
00:23:16,937 --> 00:23:18,605
Drink.

266
00:23:18,773 --> 00:23:20,023
Okay, we agree on something.

267
00:23:20,191 --> 00:23:22,192
In silence.

268
00:23:28,783 --> 00:23:31,451
James:
Will you get your ass up?

269
00:23:31,619 --> 00:23:33,495
I've got a couple
of mules here.

270
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:35,705
Let's get mounted.

271
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:41,002
Come on.

272
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:44,506
I'm ready when you are.

273
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:47,884
Hey.

274
00:23:49,095 --> 00:23:50,762
Thank you.

275
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:53,139
You know, if that money
doesn't exist,

276
00:23:53,307 --> 00:23:57,310
I'm going to kill you.
I'll take my sweet time doing it too.

277
00:24:01,398 --> 00:24:03,233
(mule braying)

278
00:24:08,781 --> 00:24:11,783
Eduardo:
Shouldn't we move faster?

279
00:24:11,951 --> 00:24:15,245
James: Last time you moved faster
you killed your horse.

280
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:17,413
Don't you remember that?

281
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:19,624
I wouldn't say
I killed my horse.

282
00:24:19,792 --> 00:24:21,876
You wouldn't, huh?
What would you say?

283
00:24:22,044 --> 00:24:24,504
Hey, who do you
think you are?

284
00:24:24,672 --> 00:24:27,048
We could get shot
any minute now

285
00:24:27,216 --> 00:24:30,635
- and you acting like nothing...
- What? Come on.

286
00:24:30,803 --> 00:24:34,222
Enough already!
Go to hell, man!

287
00:24:34,390 --> 00:24:36,975
Go to fucking hell!

288
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:44,941
(horses approaching)

289
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:20,143
Eduardo: The last miner left
eight years ago.

290
00:25:20,311 --> 00:25:24,105
There were 10,000 people
living here at one point.

291
00:25:24,273 --> 00:25:27,400
Patiño was convinced
he could bleed a little more out of it.

292
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:29,944
So when I came over
from Spain,

293
00:25:30,112 --> 00:25:31,946
he sent me here
and had me searching

294
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:34,449
six months for nothing.

295
00:25:34,617 --> 00:25:38,620
I know this mine
like I dug it myself.

296
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:40,914
You'd better.

297
00:25:50,007 --> 00:25:53,009
Are you going to kill me
when you get the money?

298
00:25:53,177 --> 00:25:56,429
(chuckles) Come on,
let's get this over with.

299
00:25:58,474 --> 00:26:00,642
Wait.

300
00:26:03,646 --> 00:26:06,231
I have no reason
to trust you either.

301
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:09,525
There is a lot of money
at stake.

302
00:26:09,693 --> 00:26:11,778
Where did you get
that antique?

303
00:26:11,946 --> 00:26:14,030
I'm not so bad
with Bolivian women.

304
00:26:15,658 --> 00:26:18,243
So you're going to
shoot me now?

305
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,744
Huh?

306
00:26:19,912 --> 00:26:23,122
No, I don't want to.

307
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:25,708
We've been together for days

308
00:26:25,876 --> 00:26:27,752
and I don't even
know your name.

309
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:30,338
I can't trust someone
with no name.

310
00:26:30,506 --> 00:26:34,217
Well, you ought to trust me.

311
00:26:34,385 --> 00:26:37,095
I saved your life a couple
of times, didn't I?

312
00:26:37,263 --> 00:26:39,889
Besides, I'm not your problem.

313
00:26:40,057 --> 00:26:41,891
That's your problem
over there.

314
00:26:42,059 --> 00:26:43,476
What?

315
00:26:43,644 --> 00:26:45,311
That dust.

316
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:53,152
Those could be several of your friends
at a full gallop.

317
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:55,363
(cocks gun)

318
00:26:56,615 --> 00:26:59,659
You're empty, son.

319
00:26:59,827 --> 00:27:01,286
You son of a bitch.

320
00:27:01,453 --> 00:27:02,578
(chuckles)

321
00:27:02,746 --> 00:27:04,831
Yeah.

322
00:27:04,999 --> 00:27:08,584
You should've heard
what they called me back in Wyoming.

323
00:27:27,896 --> 00:27:30,064
Eduardo:
We are close.

324
00:27:30,232 --> 00:27:33,609
Next gallery to the left.
Watch your head.

325
00:27:33,777 --> 00:27:37,447
When did you find out
I had the other revolver?

326
00:27:37,614 --> 00:27:40,199
About 10 minutes ago.

327
00:27:48,167 --> 00:27:50,752
Giddyup, son.
Bring the light.

328
00:27:50,919 --> 00:27:53,629
I'm not a goddamn mole.

329
00:28:06,018 --> 00:28:08,019
It's all here.

330
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:10,355
I'm willing to split it now.

331
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:12,857
- What's to split?
- Sorry?

332
00:28:13,025 --> 00:28:15,068
There's nothing to split.
It's useless in here.

333
00:28:15,235 --> 00:28:17,904
I mean, if you make it out of here
alive, it might be worth something,

334
00:28:18,072 --> 00:28:21,449
but right now all you got
is your stupid gun and your lamp.

335
00:28:21,617 --> 00:28:23,618
Now how the hell
do we get out of here?

336
00:28:23,786 --> 00:28:26,579
- Just follow me.
- Yeah, that's what I've been doing.

337
00:28:26,747 --> 00:28:29,916
Come on. The mine has lots of ways
out of the mountain.

338
00:28:31,043 --> 00:28:34,170
(voices whispering)

339
00:28:41,136 --> 00:28:43,513
Now what, Mr. Engineer?

340
00:28:45,849 --> 00:28:48,976
Shoot the lights.
Leave them blind.

341
00:28:49,144 --> 00:28:51,646
Okay, here's your gun back.

342
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:56,609
- Ready?
- Ready.

343
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:01,030
- (gunshots)
- (people chattering)

344
00:29:13,252 --> 00:29:15,211
Goddamn Spaniard!

345
00:29:15,379 --> 00:29:17,296
You call this a way out?

346
00:29:17,464 --> 00:29:19,966
I could find my way out of hell
easier than this.

347
00:29:20,134 --> 00:29:22,093
Thanks to this way out,

348
00:29:22,261 --> 00:29:24,095
it'll be impossible for them

349
00:29:24,263 --> 00:29:26,264
to pick up our trail
again, old man.

350
00:29:29,226 --> 00:29:31,352
Where the hell are we?

351
00:29:44,032 --> 00:29:46,617
- We are safe.
- Safe?

352
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:49,745
You stole $50,000.
You ain't gonna be safe for long.

353
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:51,998
Well, I guess I'll have
to live with that.

354
00:29:52,166 --> 00:29:53,958
But I feel good.

355
00:29:54,126 --> 00:29:57,170
I feel better than ever.

356
00:30:06,096 --> 00:30:08,681
The name's James Blackthorn,

357
00:30:08,849 --> 00:30:10,725
Utah, United States.

358
00:30:10,893 --> 00:30:12,727
Eduardo Apodaca

359
00:30:12,895 --> 00:30:16,606
from Madrid, Spain.

360
00:30:16,773 --> 00:30:18,399
Rosario is not too far
from here.

361
00:30:18,567 --> 00:30:20,735
We can buy cheap horses
over there.

362
00:30:20,903 --> 00:30:23,029
I got me a little ranch
somewhere around here.

363
00:30:23,197 --> 00:30:25,531
We can get some rest
up there.

364
00:30:28,202 --> 00:30:30,953
Sometimes it's beautiful.

365
00:30:31,121 --> 00:30:33,498
It is that.

366
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:47,678
You kept me waiting
for an hour for that?

367
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:49,514
You in a hurry?

368
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:52,934
Sometimes this is like having
a little friend along with you,

369
00:30:53,101 --> 00:30:55,978
- maybe even better.
- Yeah.

370
00:30:57,231 --> 00:30:59,774
♪ Well, my name,
it is Sam Hall ♪

371
00:30:59,942 --> 00:31:03,194
♪ Sam Hall ♪

372
